<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Using a Donor PGA tour 96 for OEM S. Mario RPG chips hel]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=16544&amp;p=205530#p205530"><![CDATA[
It's because the PGA tour is 1L3B board (64k sram) and Mario RPG is a 1L5B (256k sram).<br /><br /><br />Edit:  should have made it more clear-- the 1L3B is <em>wired</em> for a 64k sram  ~ so moving  the 256k sram from the RPG board to the other won't work.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5779">Markfrizb</a> — Tue Oct 03, 2017 6:09 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
